  "description": "Johan Paul Boberg was a Swedish architect born on August 14th, 1884 and active since 1909. He designed a large number of private and public buildings, and organized several exhibitions. Boberg was awarded the Royal Order of the North Star, the Royal Order of Vasa, the Pro Patria Gold Medal, the Patriotic Association's Large Gold Medal, the Swedish Skiing Federation's Gold Medal, and the Corresponding Member of the Finnish Society of Architects and Engineers."
